  116. /* Switch from OCaml to C stack. */
  117. .macro SWITCH_OCAML_TO_C
  118.     /* Fill in Caml_state->current_stack->sp */
  119.         ld      TMP, Caml_state(current_stack)
  120.         sd      sp, Stack_sp(TMP)
  121.     /* Fill in Caml_state->c_stack */
  122.         ld      TMP2, Caml_state(c_stack)
  123.         sd      TMP, Cstack_stack(TMP2)
  124.         sd      sp, Cstack_sp(TMP2)
  125.     /* Switch to C stack */
  126.         mv      sp, TMP2
  127.         CFI_REMEMBER_STATE
  128. .endm

  130. /* Switch from C to OCaml stack. */
  131. .macro SWITCH_C_TO_OCAML
  132.         ld      sp, Cstack_sp(sp)
  133.         CFI_RESTORE_STATE
  134. .endm

  136. /* Save all of the registers that may be in use to a free gc_regs bucket
  137.    and store ALLOC_PTR and TRAP_PTR back to Caml_state
  138.    At the end the saved registers are placed in Caml_state(gc_regs)
  139. */
  140. .macro SAVE_ALL_REGS
  141.     /* First, save the young_ptr & exn_handler */
  142.         sd      ALLOC_PTR, Caml_state(young_ptr)
  143.         sd      TRAP_PTR, Caml_state(exn_handler)
  144.     /* Now, use TMP to point to the gc_regs bucket */
  145.         ld      TMP, Caml_state(gc_regs_buckets)
  146.         ld      TMP2, 0(TMP) /* next ptr */
  147.         sd      TMP2, Caml_state(gc_regs_buckets)
  148.     /* Save allocatable integer registers */
  149.         sd      a0, (2*8)(TMP)
  150.         sd      a1, (3*8)(TMP)
  151.         sd      a2, (4*8)(TMP)
  152.         sd      a3, (5*8)(TMP)
  153.         sd      a4, (6*8)(TMP)
  154.         sd      a5, (7*8)(TMP)
  155.         sd      a6, (8*8)(TMP)
  156.         sd      a7, (9*8)(TMP)
  157.         sd      s2, (10*8)(TMP)
  158.         sd      s3, (11*8)(TMP)
  159.         sd      s4, (12*8)(TMP)
  160.         sd      s5, (13*8)(TMP)
  161.         sd      s6, (14*8)(TMP)
  162.         sd      s7, (15*8)(TMP)
  163.         sd      s8, (16*8)(TMP)
  164.         sd      s9, (17*8)(TMP)
  165.         sd      t2, (18*8)(TMP)
  166.         sd      t3, (19*8)(TMP)
  167.         sd      t4, (20*8)(TMP)
  168.         sd      t5, (21*8)(TMP)
  169.         sd      t6, (22*8)(TMP)
  170.         sd      s0, (23*8)(TMP)
  171.     /* Save caller-save floating-point registers
  172.        (callee-saves are preserved by C functions) */
  173.         fsd     ft0, (24*8)(TMP)
  174.         fsd     ft1, (25*8)(TMP)
  175.         fsd     ft2, (26*8)(TMP)
  176.         fsd     ft3, (27*8)(TMP)
  177.         fsd     ft4, (28*8)(TMP)
  178.         fsd     ft5, (29*8)(TMP)
  179.         fsd     ft6, (30*8)(TMP)
  180.         fsd     ft7, (31*8)(TMP)
  181.         fsd     fa0, (32*8)(TMP)
  182.         fsd     fa1, (33*8)(TMP)
  183.         fsd     fa2, (34*8)(TMP)
  184.         fsd     fa3, (35*8)(TMP)
  185.         fsd     fa4, (36*8)(TMP)
  186.         fsd     fa5, (37*8)(TMP)
  187.         fsd     fa6, (38*8)(TMP)
  188.         fsd     fa7, (39*8)(TMP)
  189.         fsd     ft8, (40*8)(TMP)
  190.         fsd     ft9, (41*8)(TMP)
  191.         fsd     ft10, (42*8)(TMP)
  192.         fsd     ft11, (43*8)(TMP)
  193.         addi    TMP, TMP, 16
  194.         sd      TMP, Caml_state(gc_regs)
  195. .endm

  197. /* Undo SAVE_ALL_REGS by loading the registers saved in Caml_state(gc_regs)
  198.    and refreshing ALLOC_PTR & TRAP_PTR from Caml_state */
  199. .macro RESTORE_ALL_REGS
  200.     /* Restore a0, a1, freeing up the next ptr slot */
  201.         ld      TMP, Caml_state(gc_regs)
  202.         addi    TMP, TMP, -16
  203.     /* Restore registers */
  204.         ld      a0, (2*8)(TMP)
  205.         ld      a1, (3*8)(TMP)
  206.         ld      a2, (4*8)(TMP)
  207.         ld      a3, (5*8)(TMP)
  208.         ld      a4, (6*8)(TMP)
  209.         ld      a5, (7*8)(TMP)
  210.         ld      a6, (8*8)(TMP)
  211.         ld      a7, (9*8)(TMP)
  212.         ld      s2, (10*8)(TMP)
  213.         ld      s3, (11*8)(TMP)
  214.         ld      s4, (12*8)(TMP)
  215.         ld      s5, (13*8)(TMP)
  216.         ld      s6, (14*8)(TMP)
  217.         ld      s7, (15*8)(TMP)
  218.         ld      s8, (16*8)(TMP)
  219.         ld      s9, (17*8)(TMP)
  220.         ld      t2, (18*8)(TMP)
  221.         ld      t3, (19*8)(TMP)
  222.         ld      t4, (20*8)(TMP)
  223.         ld      t5, (21*8)(TMP)
  224.         ld      t6, (22*8)(TMP)
  225.         ld      s0, (23*8)(TMP)
  226.         fld     ft0, (24*8)(TMP)
  227.         fld     ft1, (25*8)(TMP)
  228.         fld     ft2, (26*8)(TMP)
  229.         fld     ft3, (27*8)(TMP)
  230.         fld     ft4, (28*8)(TMP)
  231.         fld     ft5, (29*8)(TMP)
  232.         fld     ft6, (30*8)(TMP)
  233.         fld     ft7, (31*8)(TMP)
  234.         fld     fa0, (32*8)(TMP)
  235.         fld     fa1, (33*8)(TMP)
  236.         fld     fa2, (34*8)(TMP)
  237.         fld     fa3, (35*8)(TMP)
  238.         fld     fa4, (36*8)(TMP)
  239.         fld     fa5, (37*8)(TMP)
  240.         fld     fa6, (38*8)(TMP)
  241.         fld     fa7, (39*8)(TMP)
  242.         fld     ft8, (40*8)(TMP)
  243.         fld     ft9, (41*8)(TMP)
  244.         fld     ft10, (42*8)(TMP)
  245.         fld     ft11, (43*8)(TMP)
  246.     /* Put gc_regs struct back in bucket linked list */
  247.         ld      TMP2, Caml_state(gc_regs_buckets)
  248.         sd      TMP2, 0(TMP) /* next ptr */
  249.         sd      TMP, Caml_state(gc_regs_buckets)
  250.     /* Reload new allocation pointer & exn handler */
  251.         ld      ALLOC_PTR, Caml_state(young_ptr)
  252.         ld      TRAP_PTR, Caml_state(exn_handler)
  253. .endm

  261. FUNCTION(caml_call_realloc_stack)
  262.     /* Save return address */
  263.         CFI_OFFSET(ra, -8)
  264.         addi    sp, sp, -16
  265.         sd      ra, 8(sp)
  266.         CFI_ADJUST(16)
  267.     /* Save all registers (including ALLOC_PTR & TRAP_PTR) */
  268.         SAVE_ALL_REGS
  269.         ld      C_ARG_1, 16(sp) /* argument */
  270.         SWITCH_OCAML_TO_C
  271.         call    PLT(caml_try_realloc_stack)
  272.         SWITCH_C_TO_OCAML
  273.         beqz    a0, 1f
  274.         RESTORE_ALL_REGS
  275.     /* Free stack space and return to caller */
  276.         ld      ra, 8(sp)
  277.         addi    sp, sp, 16
  278.         ret
  279. 1:      RESTORE_ALL_REGS
  280.     /* Raise the Stack_overflow exception */
  281.         ld      ra, 8(sp)
  282.         addi    sp, sp, 16
  283.         addi    sp, sp, 16 /* pop argument */
  284.         la      a0, caml_exn_Stack_overflow
  285.         j       L(caml_raise_exn)
  286. END_FUNCTION(caml_call_realloc_stack)

  288. FUNCTION(caml_call_gc)
  289. L(caml_call_gc):
  290.     /* Save return address */
  291.         CFI_OFFSET(ra, -8)
  292.         addi    sp, sp, -16
  293.         sd      ra, 8(sp)
  294.         CFI_ADJUST(16)
  295.     /* Store all registers (including ALLOC_PTR & TRAP_PTR) */
  296.         SAVE_ALL_REGS
  297.         SWITCH_OCAML_TO_C
  298.     /* Call the garbage collector */
  299.         call    PLT(caml_garbage_collection)
  300.         SWITCH_C_TO_OCAML
  301.         RESTORE_ALL_REGS
  302.     /* Free stack space and return to caller */
  303.         ld      ra, 8(sp)
  304.         addi    sp, sp, 16
  305.         ret
  306. END_FUNCTION(caml_call_gc)

  308. FUNCTION(caml_alloc1)
  309.         ld      TMP, Caml_state(young_limit)
  310.         addi    ALLOC_PTR, ALLOC_PTR, -16
  311.         bltu    ALLOC_PTR, TMP, L(caml_call_gc)
  312.         ret
  313. END_FUNCTION(caml_alloc1)

  315. FUNCTION(caml_alloc2)

  322. FUNCTION(caml_alloc3)

  329. FUNCTION(caml_allocN)
  330.         ld      TMP, Caml_state(young_limit)
  331.         sub     ALLOC_PTR, ALLOC_PTR, ADDITIONAL_ARG
  332.         bltu    ALLOC_PTR, TMP, L(caml_call_gc)

  336. /* Call a C function from OCaml */
  337. /* Function to call is in ADDITIONAL_ARG */

  339. FUNCTION(caml_c_call)
  340. L(caml_c_call):
  341.         CFI_OFFSET(ra, -8)
  342.         addi    sp, sp, -16
  343.         sd      ra, 8(sp)
  344.         CFI_ADJUST(16)
  345.     /* Switch form OCaml to C */
  346.         SWITCH_OCAML_TO_C
  347.     /* Make the exception handler alloc ptr available to the C code */
  348.         sd      ALLOC_PTR, Caml_state(young_ptr)
  349.         sd      TRAP_PTR, Caml_state(exn_handler)
  350.     /* Call the function */
  351.         jalr    ADDITIONAL_ARG
  352.     /* Reload alloc ptr */
  353.         ld      ALLOC_PTR, Caml_state(young_ptr)
  354.     /* Load ocaml stack */
  355.         SWITCH_C_TO_OCAML
  356.     /* Return */
  357.         ld      ra, 8(sp)
  358.         addi    sp, sp, 16
  359.         ret
  360. END_FUNCTION(caml_c_call)

  362. FUNCTION(caml_c_call_stack_args)
  363.     /* Arguments:
  364.         C arguments  : a0 to a7, fa0 to fa7
  365.         C function   : ADDITIONAL_ARG
  366.         C stack args : begin=STACK_ARG_BEGIN
  367.                        end=STACK_ARG_END */
  368.         CFI_OFFSET(ra, -8)
  369.         addi    sp, sp, -16
  370.         sd      ra, 8(sp)
  371.         CFI_ADJUST(16)
  372.     /* Switch from OCaml to C */
  373.         SWITCH_OCAML_TO_C
  374.     /* Make the exception handler alloc ptr available to the C code */
  375.         sd      ALLOC_PTR, Caml_state(young_ptr)
  376.         sd      TRAP_PTR, Caml_state(exn_handler)
  377.     /* Store sp to restore after call */
  378.         mv      s2, sp
  379.     /* Copy arguments from OCaml to C stack
  380.        NB: STACK_ARG_{BEGIN,END} are 16-byte aligned */
  381. 1:      addi    STACK_ARG_END, STACK_ARG_END, -16
  382.         bltu    STACK_ARG_END, STACK_ARG_BEGIN, 2f
  383.         ld      TMP, 0(STACK_ARG_END)
  384.         ld      TMP2, 8(STACK_ARG_END)
  385.         addi    sp, sp, -16
  386.         sd      TMP, 0(sp)
  387.         sd      TMP2, 8(sp)
  388.         CFI_ADJUST(16)
  389.         j       1b
  390. 2:  /* Call the function */
  391.         jalr    ADDITIONAL_ARG
  392.     /* Restore stack */
  393.         mv      sp, s2
  394.     /* Reload alloc ptr */
  395.         ld      ALLOC_PTR, Caml_state(young_ptr)
  396.     /* Switch from C to OCaml */
  397.         SWITCH_C_TO_OCAML
  398.     /* Return */
  399.         ld      ra, 8(sp)
  400.         addi    sp, sp, 16
  401.         ret
  402. END_FUNCTION(caml_c_call_stack_args)

  404. /* Start the OCaml program */

  406. FUNCTION(caml_start_program)
  407.     /* domain state is passed as arg from C */
  408.         mv      TMP, C_ARG_1
  409.         la      TMP2, caml_program

  411. /* Code shared with caml_callback* */
  412. /* Address of domain state is in TMP */
  413. /* Address of OCaml code to call is in TMP2 */
  414. /* Arguments to the OCaml code are in a0...a7 */

  416. L(jump_to_caml):
  417.     /* Set up stack frame and save callee-save registers */
  418.         CFI_OFFSET(ra, -200)
  419.         addi    sp, sp, -208
  420.         sd      ra, 8(sp)
  421.         CFI_ADJUST(208)
  422.         sd      s0, (2*8)(sp)
  423.         sd      s1, (3*8)(sp)
  424.         sd      s2, (4*8)(sp)
  425.         sd      s3, (5*8)(sp)
  426.         sd      s4, (6*8)(sp)
  427.         sd      s5, (7*8)(sp)
  428.         sd      s6, (8*8)(sp)
  429.         sd      s7, (9*8)(sp)
  430.         sd      s8, (10*8)(sp)
  431.         sd      s9, (11*8)(sp)
  432.         sd      s10, (12*8)(sp)
  433.         sd      s11, (13*8)(sp)
  434.         fsd     fs0, (14*8)(sp)
  435.         fsd     fs1, (15*8)(sp)
  436.         fsd     fs2, (16*8)(sp)
  437.         fsd     fs3, (17*8)(sp)
  438.         fsd     fs4, (18*8)(sp)
  439.         fsd     fs5, (19*8)(sp)
  440.         fsd     fs6, (20*8)(sp)
  441.         fsd     fs7, (21*8)(sp)
  442.         fsd     fs8, (22*8)(sp)
  443.         fsd     fs9, (23*8)(sp)
  444.         fsd     fs10, (24*8)(sp)
  445.         fsd     fs11, (25*8)(sp)
  446.     /* Load domain state pointer from argument */
  447.         mv      DOMAIN_STATE_PTR, TMP
  448.     /* Reload allocation pointer */
  449.         ld      ALLOC_PTR, Caml_state(young_ptr)
  450.     /* Build (16-byte aligned) struct c_stack_link on the C stack */
  451.         ld      t2, Caml_state(c_stack)
  452.         addi    sp, sp, -32
  453.         sd      t2, Cstack_prev(sp)
  454.         sd      x0, Cstack_stack(sp)
  455.         sd      x0, Cstack_sp(sp)
  456.         CFI_ADJUST(32)
  457.         sd      sp, Caml_state(c_stack)
  458.     /* Load the OCaml stack */
  459.         ld      t2, Caml_state(current_stack)
  460.         ld      t2, Stack_sp(t2)
  461.     /* Store the gc_regs for callbacks during a GC */
  462.         ld      t3, Caml_state(gc_regs)
  463.         addi    t2, t2, -8
  464.         sd      t3, 0(t2)
  465.     /* Store the stack pointer to allow DWARF unwind */
  466.         addi    t2, t2, -8
  467.         sd      sp, 0(t2) /* C_stack_sp */
  468.     /* Setup a trap frame to catch exceptions escaping the OCaml code */
  469.         ld      t3, Caml_state(exn_handler)
  470.         la      t4, L(trap_handler)
  471.         addi    t2, t2, -16
  472.         sd      t3, 0(t2)
  473.         sd      t4, 8(t2)
  474.         mv      TRAP_PTR, t2
  475.     /* Switch stacks and call the OCaml code */
  476.         mv      sp, t2
  477.         CFI_REMEMBER_STATE
  478.     /* Call the OCaml code */
  479.         jalr    TMP2
  480. L(caml_retaddr):
  481.     /* Pop the trap frame, restoring Caml_state->exn_handler */
  482.         ld      t2, 0(sp)
  483.         addi    sp, sp, 16
  484.         CFI_ADJUST(-16)
  485.         sd      t2, Caml_state(exn_handler)
  486. L(return_result):
  487.     /* Restore GC regs */
  488.         ld      t2, 0(sp)
  489.         ld      t3, 8(sp)
  490.         addi    sp, sp, 16
  491.         CFI_ADJUST(-16)
  492.         sd      t3, Caml_state(gc_regs)
  493.     /* Update allocation pointer */
  494.         sd      ALLOC_PTR, Caml_state(young_ptr)
  495.     /* Return to C stack */
  496.         ld      t2, Caml_state(current_stack)
  497.         sd      sp, Stack_sp(t2)
  498.         ld      t3, Caml_state(c_stack)
  499.         mv      sp, t3
  500.         CFI_RESTORE_STATE
  501.     /* Pop the struct c_stack_link */
  502.         ld      t2, Cstack_prev(sp)
  503.         addi    sp, sp, 32
  504.         CFI_ADJUST(-32)
  505.         sd      t2, Caml_state(c_stack)
  506.     /* Reload callee-save register and return address */
  507.         ld      s0, (2*8)(sp)
  508.         ld      s1, (3*8)(sp)
  509.         ld      s2, (4*8)(sp)
  510.         ld      s3, (5*8)(sp)
  511.         ld      s4, (6*8)(sp)
  512.         ld      s5, (7*8)(sp)
  513.         ld      s6, (8*8)(sp)
  514.         ld      s7, (9*8)(sp)
  515.         ld      s8, (10*8)(sp)
  516.         ld      s9, (11*8)(sp)
  517.         ld      s10, (12*8)(sp)
  518.         ld      s11, (13*8)(sp)
  519.         fld     fs0, (14*8)(sp)
  520.         fld     fs1, (15*8)(sp)
  521.         fld     fs2, (16*8)(sp)
  522.         fld     fs3, (17*8)(sp)
  523.         fld     fs4, (18*8)(sp)
  524.         fld     fs5, (19*8)(sp)
  525.         fld     fs6, (20*8)(sp)
  526.         fld     fs7, (21*8)(sp)
  527.         fld     fs8, (22*8)(sp)
  528.         fld     fs9, (23*8)(sp)
  529.         fld     fs10, (24*8)(sp)
  530.         fld     fs11, (25*8)(sp)
  531.         ld      ra, 8(sp)
  532.         addi    sp, sp, 208
  533.         CFI_ADJUST(-208)
  534.     /* Return to C caller */
  535.         ret
  536. END_FUNCTION(caml_start_program)

  538. /* The trap handler */

  540.         .align  2
  541. L(trap_handler):
  542.         CFI_STARTPROC
  543.     /* Save exception pointer */
  544.         sd      TRAP_PTR, Caml_state(exn_handler)
  545.     /* Encode exception pointer */
  546.         ori     a0, a0, 2
  547.     /* Return it */
  548.         j       L(return_result)
  549.         CFI_ENDPROC

  551. /* Exceptions */

  553. .macro JUMP_TO_TRAP_PTR
  554.     /* Cut stack at current trap handler */
  555.         mv      sp, TRAP_PTR
  556.     /* Pop previous handler and jump to it */
  557.         ld      TMP, 8(sp)
  558.         ld      TRAP_PTR, 0(sp)
  559.         addi    sp, sp, 16
  560.         jr      TMP
  561. .endm

  563. /* Raise an exception from OCaml */
  564. FUNCTION(caml_raise_exn)
  565. L(caml_raise_exn):
  566.     /* Test if backtrace is active */
  567.         ld      TMP, Caml_state(backtrace_active)
  568.         bnez    TMP, 2f
  569. 1:
  570.         JUMP_TO_TRAP_PTR
  571. 2:  /* Zero backtrace_pos */
  572.         sd      x0, Caml_state(backtrace_pos)
  573. L(caml_reraise_exn_stash):
  574.     /* Preserve exception bucket in callee-save register s2 */
  575.         mv      s2, a0
  576.     /* Stash the backtrace */
  577.                                   /* arg1: exn bucket, already in a0 */
  578.         mv      a1, ra            /* arg2: pc of raise */
  579.         mv      a2, sp            /* arg3: sp of raise */
  580.         mv      a3, TRAP_PTR      /* arg4: sp of handler */
  581.     /* Switch to C stack */
  582.         ld      TMP, Caml_state(c_stack)
  583.         mv      sp, TMP
  584.         call    PLT(caml_stash_backtrace)
  585.     /* Restore exception bucket and raise */
  586.         mv      a0, s2
  587.         j       1b
  588. END_FUNCTION(caml_raise_exn)

  590. FUNCTION(caml_reraise_exn)
  591.         ld      TMP, Caml_state(backtrace_active)
  592.         bnez    TMP, L(caml_reraise_exn_stash)
  593.         JUMP_TO_TRAP_PTR
  594. END_FUNCTION(caml_reraise_exn)

  596. /* Raise an exception from C */

  598. FUNCTION(caml_raise_exception)
  599.     /* Load the domain state ptr */
  600.         mv      DOMAIN_STATE_PTR, C_ARG_1
  601.     /* Load the exception bucket */
  602.         mv      a0, C_ARG_2
  603.     /* Reload trap ptr and alloc ptr */
  604.         ld      TRAP_PTR, Caml_state(exn_handler)
  605.         ld      ALLOC_PTR, Caml_state(young_ptr)
  606.     /* Discard the C stack pointer and reset to ocaml stack */
  607.         ld      TMP, Caml_state(current_stack)
  608.         ld      TMP, Stack_sp(TMP)
  609.         mv      sp, TMP
  610.     /* Restore frame and link on return to OCaml */
  611.         ld      ra, 8(sp)
  612.         addi    sp, sp, 16
  613.         j       L(caml_raise_exn)
  614. END_FUNCTION(caml_raise_exception)

  616. /* Callback from C to OCaml */

  618. FUNCTION(caml_callback_asm)
  619.     /* Initial shuffling of arguments */
  620.     /* (a0 = Caml_state, a1 = closure, 0(a2) = first arg) */
  621.         mv      TMP, a0
  622.         ld      a0, 0(a2)           /* a0 = first arg */
  623.                                     /* a1 = closure environment */
  624.         ld      TMP2, 0(a1)          /* code pointer */
  625.         j       L(jump_to_caml)
  626. END_FUNCTION(caml_callback_asm)

  628. FUNCTION(caml_callback2_asm)
  629.     /* Initial shuffling of arguments */
  630.     /* (a0 = Caml_state, a1 = closure, 0(a2) = arg1, 8(a2) = arg2) */
  631.         mv      TMP, a0
  632.         mv      TMP2, a1
  633.         ld      a0, 0(a2) /* a0 = first arg */
  634.         ld      a1, 8(a2) /* a1 = second arg */
  635.         mv      a2, TMP2   /* a2 = closure environment */
  636.         la      TMP2, caml_apply2
  637.         j       L(jump_to_caml)
  638. END_FUNCTION(caml_callback2_asm)

  640. FUNCTION(caml_callback3_asm)
  641.     /* Initial shuffling of arguments */
  642.     /* (a0 = Caml_state, a1 = closure, 0(a2) = arg1, 8(a2) = arg2,
  643.         16(a2) = arg3) */
  644.         mv      TMP, a0
  645.         mv      a3, a1       /* a3 = closure environment */
  646.         ld      a0, 0(a2)    /* a0 = first arg */
  647.         ld      a1, 8(a2)    /* a1 = second arg */
  648.         ld      a2, 16(a2)   /* a2 = third arg */
  649.         la      TMP2, caml_apply3
  650.         j       L(jump_to_caml)
  651. END_FUNCTION(caml_callback3_asm)

  653. /* Fibers */

  655. /* Switch between OCaml stacks. Clobbers TMP and switches TRAP_PTR
  656.    Preserves old_stack and new_stack registers */
  657. .macro SWITCH_OCAML_STACKS old_stack, new_stack
  658.     /* Save frame pointer and return address for old_stack */
  659.         addi    sp, sp, -16
  660.         sd      ra, 8(sp)
  661.         CFI_ADJUST(16)
  662.     /* Save OCaml SP and exn_handler in the stack info */
  663.         sd      sp, Stack_sp(\old_stack)
  664.         sd      TRAP_PTR, Stack_exception(\old_stack)
  665.     /* switch stacks */
  666.         sd      \new_stack, Caml_state(current_stack)
  667.         ld      TMP, Stack_sp(\new_stack)
  668.         mv      sp, TMP
  669.     /* restore exn_handler for new stack */
  670.         ld      TRAP_PTR, Stack_exception(\new_stack)
  671.     /* Restore frame pointer and return address for new_stack */
  672.         ld      ra, 8(sp)
  673.         addi    sp, sp, 16
  674. .endm

  676. /*
  677. * A continuation is a one word object that points to a fiber. A fiber [f] will
  678. * point to its parent at Handler_parent(Stack_handler(f)). In the following,
  679. * the [last_fiber] refers to the last fiber in the linked-list formed by the
  680. * parent pointer.
  681. */

  683. FUNCTION(caml_perform)
  684.     /*  a0: effect to perform
  685.         a1: freshly allocated continuation */
  686.         ld      a2, Caml_state(current_stack) /* a2 := old stack */
  687.         addi    a3, a2, 1 /* a3 := Val_ptr(old stack) */
  688.         sd      a3, 0(a1) /* Iniitalize continuation */
  689. L(do_perform):
  690.     /*  a0: effect to perform
  691.         a1: continuation
  692.         a2: old_stack
  693.         a3: last_fiber */

  695.         ld      t3, Stack_handler(a2)  /* t3 := old stack -> handler */
  696.         ld      t4, Handler_parent(t3) /* t4 := parent stack */
  697.         beqz    t4, 1f
  698.         SWITCH_OCAML_STACKS a2, t4
  699.     /*  we have to null the Handler_parent after the switch because
  700.         the Handler_parent is needed to unwind the stack for backtraces */
  701.         sd      x0, Handler_parent(t3) /* Set parent of performer to NULL */
  702.         ld      TMP, Handler_effect(t3)
  703.         mv      a2, a3                 /* a2 := last_fiber */
  704.         mv      a3, TMP                /* a3 := effect handler */
  705.         tail    PLT(caml_apply3)
  706. 1:
  707.     /*  switch back to original performer before raising Effect.Unhandled
  708.         (no-op unless this is a reperform) */
  709.         ld      t4, 0(a1) /* load performer stack from continuation */
  710.         addi    t4, t4, -1 /* t4 := Ptr_val(t4) */
  711.         ld      t3, Caml_state(current_stack)
  712.         SWITCH_OCAML_STACKS t3, t4
  713.     /*  No parent stack. Raise Effect.Unhandled. */
  714.         la      ADDITIONAL_ARG, caml_raise_unhandled_effect
  715.         j       L(caml_c_call)
  716. END_FUNCTION(caml_perform)

  718. FUNCTION(caml_reperform)
  719.     /*  a0: effect to perform
  720.         a1: continuation
  721.         a2: last_fiber */
  722.         ld      TMP, Stack_handler_from_cont(a2)
  723.         ld      a2, Caml_state(current_stack) /* a2 := old stack */
  724.         sd      a2, Handler_parent(TMP) /* Append to last_fiber */
  725.         addi    a3, a2, 1 /* a3 (last_fiber) := Val_ptr(old stack) */
  726.         j       L(do_perform)
  727. END_FUNCTION(caml_reperform)

  729. FUNCTION(caml_resume)
  730.     /*  a0: new fiber
  731.         a1: fun
  732.         a2: arg */
  733.         addi    a0, a0, -1 /* a0 = Ptr_val(a0) */
  734.         ld      a3, 0(a1)  /* code pointer */
  735.     /* Check if stack null, then already used */
  736.         beqz    a0, 2f
  737.     /* Find end of list of stacks (put in t2) */
  738.         mv      TMP, a0
  739. 1:      ld      t2, Stack_handler(TMP)
  740.         ld      TMP, Handler_parent(t2)
  741.         bnez    TMP, 1b
  742.     /* Add current stack to the end */
  743.         ld      t3, Caml_state(current_stack)
  744.         sd      t3, Handler_parent(t2)
  745.         SWITCH_OCAML_STACKS t3, a0
  746.         mv      a0, a2
  747.         jr      a3
  748. 2:      la      ADDITIONAL_ARG, caml_raise_continuation_already_resumed
  749.         j       L(caml_c_call)
  750. END_FUNCTION(caml_resume)

  752. /* Run a function on a new stack, then either
  753.    return the value or invoke exception handler */
  754. FUNCTION(caml_runstack)
  755.     /*  a0: fiber
  756.         a1: fun
  757.         a2: arg */
  758.         CFI_OFFSET(ra, -8)
  759.         addi    sp, sp, -16
  760.         sd      ra, 8(sp)
  761.         CFI_ADJUST(16)
  762.         addi    a0, a0, -1  /* a0 := Ptr_val(a0) */
  763.         ld      a3, 0(a1)   /* code pointer */
  764.     /*  save old stack pointer and exception handler */
  765.         ld      t2, Caml_state(current_stack) /* t2 := old stack */
  766.         sd      sp, Stack_sp(t2)
  767.         sd      TRAP_PTR, Stack_exception(t2)
  768.     /* Load new stack pointer and set parent */
  769.         ld      TMP, Stack_handler(a0)
  770.         sd      t2, Handler_parent(TMP)
  771.         sd      a0, Caml_state(current_stack)
  772.         ld      t3, Stack_sp(a0) /* t3 := sp of new stack */
  773.     /* Create an exception handler on the target stack
  774.        after 16byte DWARF & gc_regs block (which is unused here) */
  775.         addi    t3, t3, -32
  776.         la      TMP, L(fiber_exn_handler)
  777.         sd      TMP, 8(t3)
  778.     /* link the previous exn_handler so that copying stacks works */
  779.         ld      TMP, Stack_exception(a0)
  780.         sd      TMP, 0(t3)
  781.         mv      TRAP_PTR, t3
  782.     /* Switch to the new stack */
  783.         mv      sp, t3
  784.         CFI_REMEMBER_STATE
  785.     /* Call the function on the new stack */
  786.         mv      a0, a2
  787.         jalr    a3
  788. L(frame_runstack):
  789.         addi    t2, sp, 32 /* t2 := stack_handler */
  790.         ld      s2, Handler_value(t2) /* saved across C call */
  791. 1:
  792.         mv      s3, a0     /* save return across C call */
  793.         ld      a0, Caml_state(current_stack) /* arg to caml_free_stack */
  794.     /* restore parent stack and exn_handler into Caml_state */
  795.         ld      TMP, Handler_parent(t2)
  796.         sd      TMP, Caml_state(current_stack)
  797.         ld      TRAP_PTR, Stack_exception(TMP)
  798.         sd      TRAP_PTR, Caml_state(exn_handler)
  799.     /* free old stack by switching directly to c_stack;
  800.        is a no-alloc call */
  801.         ld      s4, Stack_sp(TMP) /* saved across C call */
  802.         CFI_RESTORE_STATE
  803.         CFI_REMEMBER_STATE
  804.         ld      TMP, Caml_state(c_stack)
  805.         mv      sp, TMP
  806.         call    PLT(caml_free_stack)
  807.     /* switch directly to parent stack with correct return */
  808.         mv      a0, s3
  809.         mv      a1, s2
  810.         mv      sp, s4
  811.         CFI_RESTORE_STATE
  812.         ld      TMP, 0(s2)  /* code pointer */
  813.     /* Invoke handle_value (or handle_exn) */
  814.         ld      ra, 8(sp)
  815.         addi    sp, sp, 16
  816.         CFI_ADJUST(-16)
  817.         jr      TMP
  818. L(fiber_exn_handler):
  819.         addi    t2, sp, 16  /* t2 := stack_handler */
  820.         ld      s2, Handler_exception(t2)
  821.         j       1b
  822. END_FUNCTION(caml_runstack)

  824. FUNCTION(caml_ml_array_bound_error)
  825.     /* Load address of [caml_array_bound_error_asm] in ADDITIONAL_ARG */
  826.         la      ADDITIONAL_ARG, caml_array_bound_error_asm
  827.     /* Call that function */
  828.         j       L(caml_c_call)
  829. END_FUNCTION(caml_ml_array_bound_error)

  831.         .globl  caml_system__code_end
  832. caml_system__code_end:
